-- Yoshinoya to Increase Number of Outlets in Southeast Asia, Nikkei Reports
-- Keiko Ujikane
-- 2010-06-26T01:22:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-26/yoshinoya-to-increase-number-of-outlets-in-southeast-asia-nikkei-reports.html

          
          
             Yoshinoya Holdings Co. is aiming to
increase the number of its beef bowl restaurants in Southeast
Asia to between 300 and 400 stores over the next 10 years, the
Nikkei newspaper reported, without citing where it obtained the
information.  
 Yoshinoya, which opened an outlet in Indonesia yesterday,
is trying to set up 100 franchise locations in the country by
2020, the newspaper said. It is also aiming to open restaurants
in Thailand and Vietnam, the Nikkei said, citing Ryusuke Tanaka,
president of Yoshinoya International Co.  
 The company also wants to increase the number of outlets it
has in China to 1,000 over the next 10 years from the 200
locations it currently has, the newspaper said.   
